# Testing Rules

## Test Structure
- Follow Arrange-Act-Assert pattern.
- One logical assertion per test. Test name describes the expected behavior.
- Keep tests independent — no shared mutable state between tests.

## Coverage
- Every new feature needs at least one happy-path test and one error-case test.
- Bug fixes must include a regression test that reproduces the original bug.

## Mocking
- Mock at the boundary (network, filesystem, time), not internal modules.
- Prefer dependency injection over monkey-patching.

## Reminder
When you finish editing test files, suggest: "Run `>om:check` to validate the full test suite."
